                            What Lurks Below - Sebarus's Author Page
                        </div>
                    

                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        












<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1 id="toc0"><span><span style="font-size:200%;"><span style="color:black">W̵͔̟̃̆̆̽ͅͅę̸̮̣̗̌̇̆͌l̵̛͔̱͙͖̈́͝c̶̘̖͈̓o̷̙̙͗̓͝m̷̠̤͎̔ͅe̷̩̜̫̽̃̕,̵̻͚͍̺͂̊͠ ̶̢̓͊̇t̶͓͌͝r̶̗̀̈́̌ͅa̵̺̗̳̔v̵̯̰̱͒̓̀ȩ̶͈̠̏̈́l̶̺͈̏̆̐̑e̸͎͊͑̽̕r̷̝͛͑͝</span></span></span></h1>
</div>
<br />
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><em>*Ahem*</em></p>
</div>
<br />
As I was saying, welcome, traveler. Haven't seen a lot of souls ever since they locked me down here. Why not stay a while, and listen to an old thing ramble? You don't look like you're in a hurry either, not with that leg of yours. Be careful around the edge, so you don't fall in here. It's a long way down.
<p>Oh, why am I down here, you ask. I'm here because many choose to fear that which they don't understand, and many choose to destroy, or in my case lock away, what they fear. I have been here for a long time, so long that most souls in this facility have forgotten that I'm even here. I have had a lot of free time. Want to know what I do with that free time?</p>
<p>I write. With will as my quill and the fabric of reality as my canvas, I write, and my words shape reality.</p>


<p>What? Sorry, I was just talking to another friend of mine. Do you want to see what other lives my words have molded?</p>
<hr />
<script type="text/javascript" src="http://d3g0gp89917ko0.cloudfront.net/v--3e3a6f7dbcc9/common--javascript/yahooui/tabview-min.js">
</script>
<div id="wiki-tabview-da0070a720792e71c779cde96b6a8736" class="yui-navset">
<ul class="yui-nav">
<li class="selected"><a href="javascript:;"><em>SCPs</em></a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:;"><em>Tales</em></a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:;"><em>GoI Formats</em></a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:;"><em>Other</em></a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:;"><em>Hall Of Fame</em></a></li>
<li><a href="javascript:;"><em>Serious Shit</em></a></li>
</ul>
<div class="yui-content">
<div id="wiki-tab-0-0">
<div style="text-align: left;">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc1"><span><a href="/scp-4823">SCP-4823 - The Whole World Has Gone Bananas!</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>The main anomaly of SCP-4823 is a localized trans-dimensional two-way gateway in place of fruit flesh. The gateway becomes exposed when the banana is peeled, which can only be done halfway. Upon exposure, the gateway will draw the peeler in, exposing them to a noodle effect caused by a strong non-homogenous gravitational field, in order for them to fit through.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This was my first skip, and it has exceeded all my wildest dreams. A bit of context: while I only became a member of the site in 2018 and active in the community in 2019, I have been an active lurker here since 2012-2013. I enjoyed reading the site, but the community always seemed distant to me somehow. The fact that I'm now part of it feels&#8230; weird, and the fact that I have produced content for it even weirder. When I made this, I was proud of just getting something on the site. I expected this to reach maybe +20, and I would have been happy with that. But, against all of my expectations, it got into the Reviewer's Spotlight (thank you <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kilonova" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5865635); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5865635&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="Kilonova" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5865635)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kilonova" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5865635); return false;">Kilonova</a></span>) and the rating just soared. After that, people have made fan art and audio adaptations and translations of it, it's appeared (briefly) in a Markiplier video and it's just&#8230; mind blowing to me. On the September of 2020 it also became the first article on the site to have ever been both Reviewer's spotlighted <em>and</em> featured (thank you <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ocuin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6104981); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6104981&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="OCuin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6104981)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ocuin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6104981); return false;">OCuin</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/flopmind" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6407594); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6407594&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="Flopmind" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6407594)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/flopmind" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6407594); return false;">Flopmind</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/redesert" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6380468); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6380468&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="REDESERT" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6380468)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/redesert" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(6380468); return false;">REDESERT</a></span>), which is even more insane.</p>
<p>Oh, a few fun facts: This was actually inspired by a dumb JoJo meme posted in the WL Discord by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rounderhouse" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4187885); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4187885&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="Rounderhouse" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4187885)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/rounderhouse" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4187885); return false;">Rounderhouse</a></span>, and every character in this skip is actually named after different banana varieties.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc2"><span><a href="/scp-5535">SCP-5535 - When Even Your Hand Hates You</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>SCP-5535 was arrested for the murder of its wife and the attempted murder of its child in 13/07/2016. The subject claimed that it had lost control over its left hand, which had then choked its wife to death against its will.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I don't have a lot to say about this. I made it in one day, after getting the idea from wiggling my fingers in the bathroom mirror.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc3"><span><a href="/scp-5063">SCP-5063 - Driving The Turtles To Market</a></span></h3>
<p><em>&quot;You're here because you found out that the can is magic. I figured that in a world with things like the can and people like the person who made it, there must be someone responsible for keeping it out of the public eye. Am I correct?&quot;</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This was my <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/exquisite-corpse-contest">CorpseCon</a> entry, and thus a collab with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stop1010" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5915710); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5915710&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="stop1010" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5915710)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/stop1010" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5915710); return false;">stop1010</a></span>. Making it was a bit of a struggle, and went through a lot of research, brainstorming, critique, editing, trimming, etc. At the end of the day though, I'm pretty happy with how it turned out.</p>
<p>This is basically a critique on the ecological impact of capitalism and its unsustainability, based on an actual culinary trend which lead to the decimation of the snapping turtle population in real life. It was an interesting topic to research and write about, and I'm glad this project made me do that.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="text-align: left;">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc4"><span><a href="/scp-5137">SCP-5137 - Friendship Is Only Skin Deep</a></span></h3>
<p><em>&quot;When in close proximity to a living human, SCP-5137 will split down the middle and attempt to envelop the individual. If unobstructed, SCP-5137 will morph in size and coloration until it is indistinguishable from the subject's actual skin. SCP-5137 refer to this behavior as 'hugging'.&quot;</em></p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This was my first real attempt at horror, and it kind of shows. Like with 5063, I tried going for something reminiscent of Series 1 tropes, in this case a murder monster instead of a thing that does a thing, but with a modern twist. Unlike 5063 however, it didn't do very well. It's fine though, I'm happy enough with it, and while being my lowest rated work at the time of writing, it's been steadily going up and it's not gonna fall into deletion anytime soon. Hopefully.</p>
<p>5137 is also a good example of inspiration coming from the weirdest of places. I have a bad habit of picking on the skin of my fingers, and the thought of &quot;what if you made a construct out of skin&quot; hit me while I was doing that. I have no idea where the friendship aspect of it came from.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc5"><span><a href="/singed-books-and-broken-worlds">Singed Books And Broken Worlds</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>There was a silent beat, as everything fell quiet and still. Then, chaos broke out. The space was filled with a loud groan and then a loud boom, as the Way violently collapsed, sending a wave of uncontained magical energy rushing forwards.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This was made for the first day of JamCon 2020, when the theme was &quot;EXPLOSIONS&quot;. I wrote this in the span of maybe 4 hours in the middle of the night. It was exhausting but I'm pretty proud of how this turned out.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc6"><span><a href="/lantern-bearer">Lantern Bearer</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>However, of all the peculiar jobs in The Pillars, the most essential of all is that of the lantern bearers. The light of the lanterns you see, doesn't just provide well-appreciated visibility in the foggy streets of The Pillars, but it also keeps at bay The-Shapes-In-The-Fog.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The first article featuring a Free Port I'm trying to establish, The Pillars. It was also made for <a href="/monthly-prompts">Monthly Prompts</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1581620&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="DarkStuff" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1581620)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/darkstuff" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1581620); return false;">DarkStuff</a></span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc7"><span><a href="/the-blood-that-binds-us">The Blood That Binds Us</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>Chompy in tow, Jeremy walks into the joint living room and kitchen, where a woman in a green dress and a petticoat is busy chopping something. Hearing the boy come in, she turns, revealing her mutilated and fingerless hand and a bloody knife held in the other.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>CotBG saw a shift from always being the bad guys to being more neutral a long time ago, I feel like sarkicists are still mostly seen as the villains, which I'm not a fan of. There's been a few articles about good proto-sarkics, but I don't remember seeing any about neo-sarkics. So, as I've regardless always liked sarkicism, I decided that I would try to write a story about the average life of average practitioners of Nälkä. No cults, no crazy blood rituals, no nefarious secret agenda. Just a normal family with a normal life, who just happen to practice carnomancy and have flesh beast as a pet.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc8"><span><a href="/the-paintings-burn-a-crimson-red">The Paintings Burn A Crimson Red</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>The crowbar smashes into the balloon-like head of what used to be the hotel bartender, scattering thick, purple sludge across the walls and roof of the abandoned bar.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The first tale in Spectrum, the tale series that my team, consisting of myself, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/brokenordinance" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2794964); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2794964&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="BrokenOrdinance" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2794964)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/brokenordinance" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2794964); return false;">BrokenOrdinance</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncertaintycrossing" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4257427); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4257427&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1606781496" alt="UncertaintyCrossing" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4257427)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncertaintycrossing" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4257427); return false;">UncertaintyCrossing</a></span>, wrote for the Canon Renaissance Contest. It's set in the later stages of the Rat's Nest canon, so everything is weird and reality is fucked up. It tells the tale of Mirage, an angy, delusional bird-man surviving in the apocalypse and embarking on a journey to paint the greatest painting the world has ever seen.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc9"><span><a href="/critter-profile-geist">Critter Profile: Geist!</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>They say the cat would disappear during the day and come back at night. That in itself isn't especially peculiar for cats, but the mutilated animal parts that they found on their backyard the next morning sure were weird, said the father of the family.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This was kind of a last minute post for the last theme in JamCon 2020, &quot;More Than Meets The Eye&quot;. Wrote it in about 2 hours, and had enough time to get crit from one person, but out of my JamCon posts I'm the proudest of this one.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-3" style="display:none">
<div style="float: center; border: solid 4px #BB0011; width: auto; padding: 1px 15px; margin: auto; margin-top:1em; margin-bottom:1em; box-shadow: 2px 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.2);">
<h3 id="toc10"><span><a href="/what-lurks-below-sebarus-s-author-page">Author Page</a></span></h3>
<p>&quot;<em>I write. With will as my quill and the fabric of reality as my canvas, I write, and my words shape reality.</em>&quot;</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Author&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This is the page you're looking at right now, how trippy is that? It feels really surreal to finally have one on the site. Anyway, I decided to write the flavor text for this from the perspective of a skip, because why not. It's a little cringy, I admit, but who cares, it's just an author page.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-4" style="display:none">
<p>This is a space to showcase all of the cool things that people have made out of my stuff! I appreciate all of it, and I am greatly honored that people think that my writings are worthy of making more stuff out of, so it deserves to be showcased. If you have made something and it isn't here, it probably just means that I haven't seen it. In that case, if you want it up here, feel free to DM me on either Wikidot or Discord if we share a server.</p>
